    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "setup"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Setup dan Import"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "!pip install gymnasium[classic_control] -q"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import gymnasium as gym\n",
        "import math\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import matplotlib\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from collections import namedtuple, deque\n",
        "from itertools import count\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import torch.optim as optim\n",
        "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
        "\n",
        "# Setup matplotlib\n",
        "is_ipython = 'inline' in matplotlib.get_backend()\n",
        "if is_ipython:\n",
        "    from IPython import display\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.ion()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Device selection\n",
        "device = torch.device(\n",
        "    \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else\n",
        "    \"mps\" if torch.backends.mps.is_available() else\n",
        "    \"cpu\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Using device: {device}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Environment setup\n",
        "env = gym.make(\"CartPole-v1\")\n",
        "print(f\"Environment: {env}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "table-interpretation"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. 📊 Tabel Interpretasi Hyperparameter DQN\n",
        "\n",
        "| Hyperparameter | Nilai Default | Range | Fungsi | Pengaruh Nilai |\n",
        "|---|---|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **BATCH_SIZE** | 128 | 32-256 | Jumlah sampel transitions per update | ↑ Stable tapi lambat; ↓ Cepat tapi noisy |\n",
        "| **GAMMA** (γ) | 0.99 | 0.90-0.99 | Discount factor untuk future rewards | ↑ Fokus long-term; ↓ Fokus short-term |\n",
        "| **EPS_START** | 0.9 | 0.5-1.0 | Probabilitas awal exploration | ↑ Explore lebih banyak; ↓ Eksploit early |\n",
        "| **EPS_END** | 0.01 | 0.01-0.1 | Probabilitas akhir exploration | ↑ Tetap explore; ↓ Pure exploitation |\n",
        "| **EPS_DECAY** | 2500 | 1000-10000 | Kecepatan decay epsilon | ↑ Decay lambat; ↓ Decay cepat |\n",
        "| **TAU** | 0.005 | 0.001-0.01 | Update rate target network | ↑ Lebih stabil; ↓ Lebih responsif |\n",
        "| **LR** | 3e-4 | 1e-4-1e-3 | Learning rate optimizer | ↑ Cepat convergence; ↓ Stabil tapi slow |\n",
        "| **num_episodes** | 600 | 100-1000 | Jumlah episode training | ↑ Training lebih lama; ↓ Risk underfitting |\n",
        "| **memory capacity** | 10000 | 5000-50000 | Ukuran replay buffer | ↑ More diverse; ↓ Memory efficient |"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "code-explanation"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. 🔍 Penjelasan Kode Penting\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.1 State Representation\n",
        "CartPole-v1 memberikan state sebagai **vektor 4 dimensi**:\n",
        "```\n",
        "state = [position, velocity, angle, angular_velocity]\n",
        "  - position: posisi cart (-2.4 to 2.4)\n",
        "  - velocity: kecepatan cart\n",
        "  - angle: sudut pole dari vertikal (-0.42 to 0.42 radian)\n",
        "  - angular_velocity: kecepatan sudut pole\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.2 Action Selection (Epsilon-Greedy Policy)\n",
        "```python\n",
        "ε = ε_end + (ε_start - ε_end) × e^(-steps_done / ε_decay)\n",
        "\n",
        "if random() > ε:\n",
        "    action = argmax(Q(state, a))  # Exploitation: pilih best action\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    action = random()              # Exploration: random action\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.3 Reward Structure\n",
        "- **+1 point**: untuk setiap timestep pole tetap upright\n",
        "- **Episode ends**: ketika angle > 0.21 radian atau cart > 2.4 units\n",
        "- **Goal**: Maximize total reward dalam episode\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.4 Q-Value dan Bellman Equation\n",
        "```\n",
        "Q(s,a) ≈ r + γ × max_a' Q(s', a')  [Bellman Equation]\n",
        "\n",
        "Loss = (Q_predicted - Q_target)²\n",
        "     = (Q(s,a) - [r + γ × max_a' Q_target(s', a')])²\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.5 Neural Network Architecture\n",
        "```\n",
        "Input (4) → Linear(128) → ReLU → Linear(128) → ReLU → Linear(2) → Output\n",
        "              [state]                                            [Q-values for 2 actions]\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3.6 Training Loop\n",
        "```\n",
        "for each episode:\n",
        "    reset environment\n",
        "    for each timestep:\n",
        "        select_action(state) using ε-greedy\n",
        "        execute action → get (next_state, reward)\n",
        "        store transition in replay memory\n",
        "        sample batch dari memory\n",
        "        compute Q-target = r + γ × max_a' Q_target(s')\n",
        "        compute loss = MSE(Q_predicted, Q_target)\n",
        "        backprop & update policy_net\n",
        "        soft_update target_net: θ' ← τθ + (1-τ)θ'\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "replay-memory"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 4. 💾 Replay Memory Implementation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Transition: data structure untuk menyimpan (state, action, next_state, reward)\n",
        "Transition = namedtuple('Transition',\n",
        "                        ('state', 'action', 'next_state', 'reward'))\n",
        "\n",
        "class ReplayMemory(object):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Experience Replay Buffer untuk decorrelate transitions\"\"\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def __init__(self, capacity):\n",
        "        self.memory = deque([], maxlen=capacity)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def push(self, *args):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Simpan transition ke buffer\"\"\"\n",
        "        self.memory.append(Transition(*args))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def sample(self, batch_size):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Sample random batch dari memory\"\"\"\n",
        "        return random.sample(self.memory, batch_size)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def __len__(self):\n",
        "        return len(self.memory)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✓ ReplayMemory class defined\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "network-architecture"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. 🧠 DQN Network Architecture"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "class DQN(nn.Module):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Deep Q-Network untuk CartPole\n",
        "    Input: 4-dim state vector\n",
        "    Output: Q-values untuk 2 actions\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def __init__(self, n_observations, n_actions):\n",
        "        super(DQN, self).__init__()\n",
        "        # Hidden layers: 4 → 128 → 128 → 2\n",
        "        self.layer1 = nn.Linear(n_observations, 128)\n",
        "        self.layer2 = nn.Linear(128, 128)\n",
        "        self.layer3 = nn.Linear(128, n_actions)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        # x shape: (batch_size, n_observations)\n",
        "        x = F.relu(self.layer1(x))  # (batch_size, 128)\n",
        "        x = F.relu(self.layer2(x))  # (batch_size, 128)\n",
        "        return self.layer3(x)       # (batch_size, n_actions)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test network\n",
        "state, _ = env.reset()\n",
        "n_actions = env.action_space.n\n",
        "n_observations = len(state)\n",
        "\n",
        "test_net = DQN(n_observations, n_actions).to(device)\n",
        "test_state = torch.tensor(state, dtype=torch.float32, device=device).unsqueeze(0)\n",
        "test_output = test_net(test_state)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"✓ DQN Network initialized\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Input size: {n_observations}\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Output size: {n_actions}\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Test output shape: {test_output.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Sample Q-values: {test_output.detach().cpu().numpy()}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "baseline-config"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 6. ⚙️ Baseline Configuration\n",
        "\n",
        "**Konfigurasi default dari tutorial PyTorch resmi:**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# BASELINE HYPERPARAMETERS\nBASELINE_CONFIG = {\n",
        "    'BATCH_SIZE': 128,\n",
        "    'GAMMA': 0.99,\n",
        "    'EPS_START': 0.9,\n",
        "    'EPS_END': 0.01,\n",
        "    'EPS_DECAY': 2500,\n",
        "    'TAU': 0.005,\n",
        "    'LR': 3e-4,\n",
        "    'num_episodes': 600,\n",
        "    'memory_capacity': 10000\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"BASELINE CONFIGURATION (Default PyTorch Tutorial)\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "for key, value in BASELINE_CONFIG.items():\n",
        "    print(f\"  {key:.<40} {value}\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "baseline-training"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 7. 🚀 Training dengan Baseline Configuration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def create_agent(config, device):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Factory function untuk membuat agent dengan config tertentu\"\"\"\n",
        "    state, _ = env.reset()\n",
        "    n_observations = len(state)\n",
        "    n_actions = env.action_space.n\n",
        "    \n",
        "    policy_net = DQN(n_observations, n_actions).to(device)\n",
        "    target_net = DQN(n_observations, n_actions).to(device)\n",
        "    target_net.load_state_dict(policy_net.state_dict())\n",
        "    \n",
        "    optimizer = optim.AdamW(policy_net.parameters(), \n",
        "                           lr=config['LR'], amsgrad=True)\n",
        "    memory = ReplayMemory(config['memory_capacity'])\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return policy_net, target_net, optimizer, memory\n",
        "\n",
        "def select_action(state, policy_net, steps_done, config, device):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Epsilon-greedy action selection\"\"\"\n",
        "    sample = random.random()\n",
        "    eps_threshold = config['EPS_END'] + (config['EPS_START'] - config['EPS_END']) * \\\n",
        "                   math.exp(-1. * steps_done / config['EPS_DECAY'])\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if sample > eps_threshold:\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            return policy_net(state).max(1).indices.view(1, 1)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return torch.tensor([[env.action_space.sample()]], device=device, dtype=torch.long)\n",
        "\n",
        "def optimize_model(memory, policy_net, target_net, optimizer, config, device):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Satu step optimization dari batch\"\"\"\n",
        "    if len(memory) < config['BATCH_SIZE']:\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "    \n",
        "    transitions = memory.sample(config['BATCH_SIZE'])\n",
        "    batch = Transition(*zip(*transitions))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    non_final_mask = torch.tensor(tuple(map(lambda s: s is not None,\n",
        "                                            batch.next_state)), device=device, dtype=torch.bool)\n",
        "    non_final_next_states = torch.cat([s for s in batch.next_state if s is not None])\n",
        "    state_batch = torch.cat(batch.state)\n",
        "    action_batch = torch.cat(batch.action)\n",
        "    reward_batch = torch.cat(batch.reward)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    state_action_values = policy_net(state_batch).gather(1, action_batch)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    next_state_values = torch.zeros(config['BATCH_SIZE'], device=device)\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        next_state_values[non_final_mask] = target_net(non_final_next_states).max(1).values\n",
        "    \n",
        "    expected_state_action_values = (next_state_values * config['GAMMA']) + reward_batch\n",
        "    \n",
        "    criterion = nn.SmoothL1Loss()\n",
        "    loss = criterion(state_action_values, expected_state_action_values.unsqueeze(1))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "    loss.backward()\n",
        "    torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_value_(policy_net.parameters(), 100)\n",
        "    optimizer.step()\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return loss.item()\n",
        "\n",
        "def soft_update(target_net, policy_net, tau):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Soft update: θ' ← τθ + (1-τ)θ'\"\"\"\n",
        "    target_state_dict = target_net.state_dict()\n",
        "    policy_state_dict = policy_net.state_dict()\n",
        "    for key in policy_state_dict:\n",
        "        target_state_dict[key] = policy_state_dict[key] * tau + target_state_dict[key] * (1 - tau)\n",
        "    target_net.load_state_dict(target_state_dict)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✓ Training utilities defined\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def train_dqn(config, config_name=\"Baseline\", verbose=True):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Training loop untuk DQN\"\"\"\n",
        "    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Training: {config_name}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Initialize\n",
        "    policy_net, target_net, optimizer, memory = create_agent(config, device)\n",
        "    steps_done = 0\n",
        "    \n",
        "    episode_durations = []\n",
        "    episode_losses = []\n",
        "    episode_avg_losses = []\n",
        "    epsilon_values = []\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Training loop\n",
        "    for i_episode in range(config['num_episodes']):\n",
        "        state, _ = env.reset()\n",
        "        state = torch.tensor(state, dtype=torch.float32, device=device).unsqueeze(0)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        episode_loss = []\n",
        "        \n",
        "        for t in count():\n",
        "            action = select_action(state, policy_net, steps_done, config, device)\n",
        "            observation, reward, terminated, truncated, _ = env.step(action.item())\n",
        "            reward = torch.tensor([reward], device=device)\n",
        "            done = terminated or truncated\n",
        "            steps_done += 1\n",
        "            \n",
        "            if terminated:\n",
        "                next_state = None\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                next_state = torch.tensor(observation, dtype=torch.float32, device=device).unsqueeze(0)\n",
        "            \n",
        "            memory.push(state, action, next_state, reward)\n",
        "            state = next_state\n",
        "            \n",
        "            loss = optimize_model(memory, policy_net, target_net, optimizer, config, device)\n",
        "            if loss is not None:\n",
        "                episode_loss.append(loss)\n",
        "            \n",
        "            soft_update(target_net, policy_net, config['TAU'])\n",
        "            \n",
        "            if done:\n",
        "                episode_durations.append(t + 1)\n",
        "                if episode_loss:\n",
        "                    avg_loss = np.mean(episode_loss)\n",
        "                    episode_avg_losses.append(avg_loss)\n",
        "                \n",
        "                # Epsilon value at this episode\n",
        "                eps = config['EPS_END'] + (config['EPS_START'] - config['EPS_END']) * \\\n",
        "                      math.exp(-1. * steps_done / config['EPS_DECAY'])\n",
        "                epsilon_values.append(eps)\n",
        "                \n",
        "                if verbose and (i_episode + 1) % 100 == 0:\n",
        "                    avg_duration = np.mean(episode_durations[-100:])\n",
        "                    print(f\"Episode [{i_episode+1:3d}/{config['num_episodes']}] | \"\n",
        "                          f\"Duration: {t+1:3d} | \"\n",
        "                          f\"Avg100: {avg_duration:6.2f} | \"\n",
        "                          f\"ε: {eps:.4f}\")\n",
        "                break\n",
        "    \n",
        "    print(f\"Training complete! Final avg duration: {np.mean(episode_durations[-100:]):.2f}\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        'episode_durations': episode_durations,\n",
        "        'episode_avg_losses': episode_avg_losses,\n",
        "        'epsilon_values': epsilon_values,\n",
        "        'policy_net': policy_net,\n",
        "        'target_net': target_net\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# Run baseline training\nbaseline_results = train_dqn(BASELINE_CONFIG, config_name=\"BASELINE\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "modified-config"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 8. ⚡ Modified Configuration\n",
        "\n",
        "**Perubahan yang dicoba untuk meningkatkan performa:**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# MODIFIED HYPERPARAMETERS\nMODIFIED_CONFIG = {\n",
        "    'BATCH_SIZE': 64,          # ↓ Lebih cepat update, lebih noisy\n",
        "    'GAMMA': 0.95,             # ↓ Fokus lebih ke short-term rewards\n",
        "    'EPS_START': 1.0,          # ↑ Eksplorasi lebih awal\n",
        "    'EPS_END': 0.05,           # ↑ Tetap explore di akhir\n",
        "    'EPS_DECAY': 5000,         # ↑ Decay lebih lambat untuk exploration lebih lama\n",
        "    'TAU': 0.01,               # ↑ Update target network lebih cepat\n",
        "    'LR': 5e-4,                # ↑ Learning rate lebih besar\n",
        "    'num_episodes': 600,\n",
        "    'memory_capacity': 20000   # ↑ Lebih besar buffer untuk diversity\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"MODIFIED CONFIGURATION\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"\\nPerbandingan dengan Baseline:\")\n",
        "print(\"-\" * 60)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Comparison table\n",
        "for key in BASELINE_CONFIG.keys():\n",
        "    baseline_val = BASELINE_CONFIG[key]\n",
        "    modified_val = MODIFIED_CONFIG[key]\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if baseline_val != modified_val:\n",
        "        change = \"↑\" if modified_val > baseline_val else \"↓\"\n",
        "        print(f\"{key:.<30} {baseline_val:>10} → {modified_val:>10} {change}\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"{key:.<30} {baseline_val:>10} (same)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "modified-training"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 9. 🚀 Training dengan Modified Configuration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Run modified training\nmodified_results = train_dqn(MODIFIED_CONFIG, config_name=\"MODIFIED\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "comparison"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 10. 📊 Perbandingan & Analisis Komprehensif"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Performance metrics comparison\nbaseline_durations = baseline_results['episode_durations']\nmodified_durations = modified_results['episode_durations']\n",
        "\nbaseline_last_100 = np.mean(baseline_durations[-100:])\nmodified_last_100 = np.mean(modified_durations[-100:])\n",
        "\nbaseline_best_100 = max([np.mean(baseline_durations[i:i+100]) for i in range(len(baseline_durations)-100)])\nmodified_best_100 = max([np.mean(modified_durations[i:i+100]) for i in range(len(modified_durations)-100)])\n",
        "\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\nprint(\"📈 RINGKASAN PERFORMA TRAINING\")\nprint(\"=\"*70)\n",
        "\ncomparison_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Metric': [\n",
        "        'Total Episodes',\n",
        "        'Max Duration (single)',\n",
        "        'Min Duration (single)',\n",
